<br>
I also feel that feeling too strongly about things like this is dangerous to your spirituality, I think it leads to thinking things like a person has received revelation that another should take as doctrine for the whole church.  If it isnt IN the doctrine, it isnt doctrine.  I feel so strongly about this because, dh and I have seen people in our own lives fall away from the church because they felt like the leaders had fallen, because they didnt &quot;know&quot; or teach the things that they felt should be doctrine from &quot;personal revelation.&quot;   <br>
